left class=m><span class=title> Equipping a rogue for 4kon Vallon Zek</span><hr size=1> Allright, tried this is in the training area and someone suggested I try it here.   Basically, when I first started playing my rogue, I was able to equip her rather nicely for dealing with mobs and such.  The problem I had was dealing with other players.  I'm still working up my pvp skills, and I think that my equip has a lot to do with my lack of success in pvp combat.  So I've sold everything my rogue owns, and now I have 4k to play to start over on her equipment.  So I would like to get some advice, how would some of you best equip a rogue for pvp combat with 4k? <p>Tsyndria, 
Wood Elf scout of the Amazons, 
Vallon Zek


"We are nothing but a whisper on the lips of the wary, and a shadow to those we target.  In essence we do not exist, but make no mistake about it...we are here...and we are watching..."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 9:57:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipping a rogue for 4kon Vallon Zek</span><hr size=1> FBSS? ;p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 11:41:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipping a rogue for 4kon Vallon Zek</span><hr size=1> for weapons i would go for deul tombcarvers.  i love those babys, a caster will have a vary hard time getting a spell off.   <br>
<br>
what you really need is resists though.  some basic items are:<br>
<br>
2x +7 MR, bracer, gold wolf eye.  <br>
<br>
+10 MR, neck, velium wolf eye<br>
<br>
DRT(not the best ac, but the resists are vary nice for low/mid level pvp +8 magic cold fire<br>
<br>
collar of undead protection +7 poision disease<br>
<br>
as for armour, the most i ever give is a full set of banded.  all these are fairly cheap, the most expensive would be the +10 MR neck which should run you 500+ (i dont really know, my guild had a master jewler that did all of it for cost, but it costs 450 to make, so 500+ is a rough estimate)<br>
 <p>Lirin Azamia

Reaper of Tunare

www.ClanofNobles.com
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 7:55:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipping a rogue for 4kon Vallon Zek</span><hr size=1> FBSS = 8-10K on VZ<br>
<br>
First off you wanna get your standar Wolf-eye chanter made stuff.<br>
<br>
Plat Wolf-eye Neck- 150-200pp<br>
<br>
2 Wolf Eye Bracelets- 50pp each<br>
<br>
BI Crown or Ry`gorr helm- 100-150/500pp<br>
<br>
Dwarven Ringmail tunic (if you can wear it)- 20pp<br>
<br>
Sarnak Emblazened Tabard (for a medium/large race) - 250pp<br>
<br>
Ravenscale or Rygorr arms/legs/tunic/gloves-  about 200-500 each<br>
<br>
RS gloves are really nice if you can find them.<br>
<br>
Cloak of the Icebear- 100pp<br>
<br>
Troll Hide belt- 200pp<br>
<br>
Blood stained Mantle (A MUST for all rogues)- 35-50pp<br>
<br>
Mask of Deception (good luck)- No drop<br>
<br>
Split Paw hide mask- 30pp<br>
<br>
Ry`gorr Collar- 500pp<br>
<br>
<br>
MR is key, try to get that to 100+ and you'll be all set.  After that, worry about FR and CR, then PR at higher levels.  ALWAYS keep your MR gear on unless you are fighting mobs, or 1 on 1 with a pure melee, then go for AC and STR.<br>
<br>
When you get some extra plat, try to get these items:<br>
<br>
Plat Jacinth Rings (+13 MR)- 2K<br>
Earring of essance (+10 MR)- 3K<br>
Crown of Froglock Kings (+20 sv Fire/Cold)- 2-3K <p><font size=4 face=Times New Roman, serif><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</font><BR>
